URL:https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/how-to-install-and-use-nginx-on-centos-7-rhel-7/

INSTALLATION:
CENTOS 7 (cat /etc/os-release)
vi /etc/yum.repos.d/nginx.repo 
[nginx]
name=nginx repo
baseurl=http://nginx.org/packages/mainline/centos/7/$basearch/
gpgcheck=0
enabled=1


RHEL7
[nginx]
name=nginx repo
baseurl=http://nginx.org/packages/mainline/rhel/7/$basearch/
gpgcheck=0
enabled=1


yum install nginx -y

systemctl enable nginx
systemctl start nginx


yum install firewalld -y

systemctl enable firewalld
systemctl start firewalld

firewall-cmd --permanent --zone=public --add-service=http
firewall-cmd --permanent --zone=public --add-service=https
firewall-cmd --reload



    Config dir – /etc/nginx/
    Master/Global config file – /etc/nginx/nginx.conf
    Port 80 http config file – /etc/nginx/conf.d/default
    TCP ports opened by Nginx – 80 (HTTP), 443 (HTTPS)
    Document root directory – /usr/share/nginx/html


##################################################################
URL:https://www.techrepublic.com/article/how-to-enable-ssl-on-nginx/

sudo vi /etc/nginx/snippets/self-signed.conf
ssl_certificate /etc/ssl/certs/nautilus.crt;
ssl_certificate_key /etc/ssl/private/nautilus.key;

cp /tmp/nautilus.crt /etc/ssl/certs/
cp /tmp/nautilus.key /etc/ssl/private/		--(ln -s /etc/pki/tls/private /etc/ssl/)




**********************************************************************
sudo nano /etc/nginx/snippets/ssl-params.conf

In that new file, add the following contents:

ssl_protocols TLSv1.2;
ssl_prefer_server_ciphers on;
ssl_dhparam /etc/ssl/certs/dhparam.pem;
ssl_ciphers ECDHE-RSA-AES256-GCM-SHA512:DHE-RSA-AES256-GCM-SHA512:ECDHE-RSA-AES256-GCM-SHA384:DHE-RSA-AES256-GCM-SHA384:ECDHE-RSA-AES256-SHA384;
ssl_ecdh_curve secp384r1; # Requires nginx >= 1.1.0
ssl_session_timeout  10m;
ssl_session_cache shared:SSL:10m;
ssl_session_tickets off; # Requires nginx >= 1.5.9
# ssl_stapling on; # Requires nginx >= 1.3.7
# ssl_stapling_verify on; # Requires nginx => 1.3.7
resolver 8.8.8.8 8.8.4.4 valid=300s;
resolver_timeout 5s;
add_header X-Frame-Options DENY;
add_header X-Content-Type-Options nosniff;
add_header X-XSS-Protection "1; mode=block";

Because we are using a self-signed certificate, we disable SSL stapling (a method for quickly and safely determining whether or not an SSL certificate is valid). If you're not using a self-signed certificate, remove the # symbols before the two lines. You can also change the resolver line to reflect your preferred DNS servers. Save and close that file.

We also need to generate the dhparam.pem file with the command:

sudo openssl dhparam -out /etc/ssl/certs/dhparam.pem 2048

The above command will take some time.


****************************************************************************


vi /etc/nginx/conf.d/sslconfiguration.conf			--cp /etc/nginx/conf.d/default.conf /etc/nginx/conf.dsslconfiguration.conf
server{
	listen 80;

...
...
}

server {
    listen 443 ssl;
    listen [::]:443 ssl;
    include snippets/self-signed.conf;
    include snippets/ssl-params.conf;
    server_name example.com www.example.com localhost;
    root /usr/share/nginx/html;			--default document location
    index index.html index.htm index.nginx-debian.html;

}





CLIENT:
curl -Ik https://localhost
